The paper focuses on modelling human behaviour in complex systems, specifically in a department store fitting room. This suggests that the paper may fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of simulation models also suggests that the paper may belong to the Simulation and Modeling (cs.SI) sub-category. The investigation of management policies in the fitting room operation may also relate to the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-category. The use of agent-based simulation models may suggest a connection to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on modelling human behaviour may also suggest a connection to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
